General Assembly Proposed Bill No. 5029
February Session, 2026 LCO No. 311
Referred to Committee on HUMAN SERVICES
Introduced by:
REP. CANDELORA V., 86th Dist. REP. ZUPKUS, 89th Dist.
REP. O'DEA, 125th Dist. REP. ZAWISTOWSKI, 61st Dist.
REP. RUTIGLIANO, 123rd Dist. REP. CARNEY, 23rd Dist.
REP. ACKERT, 8th Dist.
AN ACT CONCERNING MEDICAID RATE INCREASES.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General
Assembly convened:
1 That Medicaid provider rates be increased in accordance with phase
2 one of a Medicaid rate study required pursuant to section 1 of public act
3 23-186 to (1) ensure such rates are competitive with provider rates
4 offered in neighboring states, and (2) improve access to quality health
5 care.
Statement of Purpose:
To increase Medicaid provider rates and improve access to quality
health care.
LCO No. 311 1 of 1

